HEADWORD: Molybdenite
<hw>Mo*lyb"de*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>molybd⟦eacute⟧nite</ets>. See <er>Molybdena</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring in soft, lead-gray, foliated
masses or scales, resembling graphite; sulphide of molybdenum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Molybdenous</ent>⟦br⟧
